<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10209166>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Pseudolepralia ellisinae Silén, 1941. Holotype UPSZTY 2469, Bonin Islands, Japan. A. General view of the colony. B. Two autozooids with complete lamina and associated avicularia. C, D. Autozooids with incomplete frontal shield at different stage. E. Close-up of avicularia with open mandibles. F. Ovicellate zooids, some with broken ooecium. Scale bars: A, F = 200 µm; B–D = 100 µm; E = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10209166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

